Lims-Naturalis Import Versie 1.0

Contents

  • Introduction

  • Getting started with the Import plugin

Introduction

With the Naturalis plugins AB1 and fasta documents can be enriched with notes values generated from CSV tab delimited Samples CRS and Bold data

Lims Naturalis API contains five(5) plugins:

  1. Import All Naturalis
  2. Samples
  3. CRS
  4. Bold
  5. Splitname

Import All Naturalis

Clicked on the "Import button" on the button menu. A dialog screen will be opened. Browse to the folders of AB1 or Fasta files to select one or more document(s).
After selecting the document(s) go to the dropdownlist Files of type: select "All Naturalis Files(*.)".
Clicked on "import" Importing document(s) will be started and showing a progressbar with the total of percentages of files imported.

Samples

Before starting to add notes to the documents, select one or more AB1 or Fasta document(s) to processed the csv sample file
There are two(2) procedures to start the "Samples" import.
  1. First procedure: Start samples import without selecting any documents

    2. Message dialog screen will be showed with the following message "Create dummy sequences for unknown extract ID's?"
    Choosing "OK" this will opened a dialogscreen to select the csv sample file. Only Dummies documents will be added with some default notes. No matching documents will be enriched with notes
    Choosing "No" No action will be taken.
    Choosing "Cancel" No action will be taken. Return to the main screen.

  2. Second procedure: Select one or more AB1 or Fasta files to start Samples import.

    3. Message dialog screen will be showed with the following message "Create dummy sequences for unknown extract ID's?"
    Choosing "OK" this will opened a dialogscreen to select the csv sample file. If there is a match between the extractid in the document and value from the csv record field "extract id" notes will be added.
    If there is no match a dummy document will be added with default notes values.
    Choosing "No"Dialog screen will appear, browse to the sample folder and select the csv sample file. Extractid that match will be enriched with notes.
    Choosing "Cancel" No action will be taken. Return to the main screen.

CRS

To start adding CRS notes value to the selected document(s), press the CRS button.
Dialog screen will be open, browse to the CRS csv file folder and select the file and press "Open". CRS notes values will be added to the document(s).

BOLD

To start adding BOLD notes value to the selected document(s), press the BOLD button.
Dialog screen will be open, browse to the BOLD csv file folder and select the file and press "Open". BOLD notes values will be added to the document(s).

Splitname

Select one or more AB1 or Fasta documents in the gridlist and press "Splitname". It will split the filename(extract) and add the extract values as notes to the selected document(s)
